              <div class="style_1">
                <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_1">Sustainability has been a cornerstone of The Island School since its creation. The goal of the school was not only to teach sustainability, but to live it. We limit our impact by producing most of the energy consumed on campus through sustainable energy producing resources, and by limiting the amount of energy the school consumes as a whole. The first is accomplished by using our 26 kW capacity solar panels, and a 10kW wind turbine; the second by teaching students to live more simply. They are limited in their luxury items to essentially a computer, lights and fans, and they are taught to use the resources that they have as efficiently as possible. The combination of producing our own energy and limiting our energy use allows students to see what it takes to live a sustainable lifestyle.  Hopefully The Island School will be able to refine its systems to the point where it can serve as a model of sustainable energy for other entities. <span class="style_2"><br /></span></p>
